{{italic title}}
'''''Estadio Deportivo''''' is a [[Spanish language]] sports daily newspaper published in [[Seville]], [[Spain]]. It is a supplement of the daily newspaper, ''[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]''.

==History and profile==
''Estadio Deportivo'' was established as a weekly newspaper in 1995.<ref name=clara>{{cite journal|author=Clara Sainz de Baranda Andújar|title=Prensa deportiva nacional y regional en España|journal=Historia y Comunicación Social|date=February 2014|volume=19|url=http://revistas.ucm.es/index.php/HICS/article/viewFile/45014/42385|accessdate=13 June 2015|language=Spanish}}</ref> On 28 August 1996 it began to be published daily.<ref name=clara/> The paper is based in Seville.<ref>{{cite journal|author2=JL Rojas Torrijos|author1=JL Manfredi Sánchez|author3=JM Herranz de la Casa|title=Entrepreneurial journalism: Sports journalism in Spain|journal=Revista Latina de Comunicación Social|date=2015|volume=70|url=http://www.ull.es/publicaciones/latina/070/paper/1035-UC/05en.html|accessdate=13 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Alejandro Quiroga|title=Football and National Identities in Spain: The Strange Death of Don Quixote|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=f5pEAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA107|accessdate=13 June 2015|date=25 October 2013|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|isbn=978-1-137-31550-2|page=107}}</ref> The former owners of the paper were Recoletos (85%) and Grupo Prensa Ibérica (15%).<ref name=clara/> In 2007 it became part of [[Unidad Editorial]].<ref name=clara/> Since 11 January 2010 ''Estadio Deportivo'' has been sold with ''El Mundo''.<ref name=clara/>

