{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}} {{Use British English|date=July 2015}} '''Haymarket Ice Rink''' was a former [[ice skating]] and [[curling]] venue in [[Edinburgh]], [[Scotland]], which opened in 1912<ref>[http://www.royalcaledoniancurlingclub.org/areas/05/prv/midl/club/Merchisto48680/aboutus.cfm History of Merchiston Curling Club] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071015135254/http://www.royalcaledoniancurlingclub.org/areas/05/prv/midl/club/Merchisto48680/aboutus.cfm |date=15 October 2007 }}</ref> and closed in 1978.<ref name=murray/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.murrayfieldicerinkltd.co.uk/history.htm|title=History|publisher=Murrayfield Ice Rink|accessdate=25 November 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120704110938/http://www.murrayfieldicerinkltd.co.uk/history.htm|archivedate=4 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
It was constructed following the availability of land resulting from the relocation of James Swan's cattle market to [[Chesser]], and was sited near to [[Haymarket railway station]].<ref name=murray>[http://www.murrayfieldinternational.com/our-history.html Murrayfield International - History] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100222051806/http://www.murrayfieldinternational.com/our-history.html |date=22 February 2010 }}</ref> The venue was home to the Bellshill Curling Club, and when it closed, the club relocated to the new curling rink at [[Murrayfield Ice Rink]].<ref>[http://www.bellshillcurlingclub.com/site/detailed_history/haymarket.html Bellshill Curling Club venues]</ref>
